        },
        "richtext_8rFEt6": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Charlotte received her formal training at the prestigious Central Saint Martins College of Art and Design, graduating with a BA in Jewellery Design in 2015.</p>"
          }
        },
        "richtext_NFTrUb": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Charlotte has gained accolades recognising her work as a designer. Featuring in magazines such as Harper’s Bazaar, British Vogue and the Sunday Telegraph as well as exhibiting at the V&A.</p>"
          }
        },
        "richtext_FRTcK6": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>After graduating she moved to New York, working for Tiffany & Co. creating jewellery collections within the luxury corporate fashion world. After eight years in the industry as a designer, Charlotte launched Phoria with the vision to create a quality line of jewellery revolving around creativity, not trends.</p>"
          }
        },
        "richtext_JTiJFa": {
          "type": "richtext",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>All phoria pieces are fully designed by Charlotte in her studio, and handmade ethically by craftsman in thailand using sustainable materials.</p>"
          }
